1 How make an object in an Amazon S3 bucket public ?
Ans To make an object in an Amazon S3 bucket public, you need to configure both the bucket policy 
    and the object's permissions.
    Option 1: Using the AWS Management Console
    1. Set Permissions for the Object:
    Go to the S3 Console.
    Navigate to the bucket where the object is stored.
    Click on the object you want to make public.
    Go to the Permissions tab.
    Scroll down to Access Control List (ACL).
    Under Public Access, you will see an option to grant public read access.
    Check the box for Everyone (public access), and enable Read permissions.
